          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">South Koreans protest</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Hundreds of protesters battled freezing temperatures in Seoul to rally for and against impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol's <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-06-01-2025-h3-8-ousting-and-arrest" target="_blank">ousting and arrest</a>. The arrest warrant, issued over his refusal to comply with investigations into a martial law decree, expired Monday at midnight. Friday’s arrest attempt failed after a tense five-hour standoff at Yoon’s residence involving police, anti-corruption investigators, and the presidential security service.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Anti-Yoon demonstrators <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-06-01-2025-h3-9-demanded" target="_blank">demanded</a> stronger efforts to arrest him, while Pro-Yoon supporters denounced his impeachment as unjust. The Corruption Investigation Office for High-Ranking Officials requested President Choi Sang-mok to order the presidential security service to stand down as the security service is mandated to protect Yoon. Meanwhile, Yoon’s lawyers have challenged the court’s detention and search warrant, claiming that a location containing military secrets cannot be searched without consent.</p>
        </mj-text>
