          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇺🇲 USA:</strong>    
          Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni met President-elect Donald Trump at his Mar-a-Lago residence in Florida, marking her as a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-06-01-2025-br1-10-key-european-ally" target="_blank">key European ally</a> for his incoming administration. Trump praised Meloni as a "fantastic woman" who took “Europe by storm." As leader of the right-wing Brothers of Italy party, Meloni has strengthened ties with Trump and Elon Musk, who headlined her 2023 convention. Discussions may have included the detention of Italian journalist Cecilia Sala in Iran, a top priority for Meloni’s government.</p>
        </mj-text>
