          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇨🇮 Ivory Coast:</strong>   
          Ivory Coast President Alassane Ouattara announced in his end-of-year address that French forces will <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-06-01-2025-br2-11-hand-over" target="_blank">hand over</a> control of their military base in Abidjan by January 2025, marking another step in France’s military withdrawal from West Africa. Ouattara highlighted the modernization of Ivory Coast’s armed forces, encouraging national pride. France has been reducing its regional military presence, recently withdrawing troops from Mali, Burkina Faso, and Niger amid anti-French sentiment and political upheavals. French troops in West Africa are expected to shrink from 2,200 to 600.</p>
        </mj-text>
